On the whole, elision is always freest in the first half of the verse. In the second hemistich of the pentameter elision is most frequent (though still not common) in the end of the last dactyl, but elision in the fifth thesis, occasional in Propertius and growing considerably in Ovid, is never found in Tibullus. Elision is increas- ingly more frequent in the hex. than in the peut, but the difference is never very large.
